               <msContents>
                  <summary>Only fragments of folio 1 remain. Folio 2 is partly attached to the binding but as it is smaller than the other folios, it presumably belongs to another manuscript.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i0">
                     <locus from="3r" to="100v">3r-100v</locus>
                     <textLang xml:lang="ar">Arabic</textLang>
                     <title type="acephalous apodous lacunous" ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT0049IHA#s38IHA">قران, First half (ǧuz’ 1-15)</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#3r">-3r</locus>وان الله لسميع عليم , اذ يريكهم الله فى منامك قليلا ولو اراكهم كثيرا لفشلتم</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="ar">
                        <locus target="#100v">-100v</locus>وقضى ربك الا تعبدوا الا اياه وبالوالدين احسانا اما \ يبلغن<note>The last word is a catchword.</note>
                     </explicit>
                     <note>3:110-17:23. Order of the folios disrupted. Folios 3r-34v: from the three last words of verse 8:42 to the end of verse 12:93. Folios 35r-83v: from the second word of verse 3:110 to the end of verse 7:5. Folios 84r-100v: from the middle of verse 13:10 to the middle of verse 17:23. Titles of sūras in red. Interlinear red comma as a verse marker. Interlinear taǧwīd markers in red. Red alifs mark long a-vowel. On fol. 37r, a section of a verse traced with red. Division markers in the margins: rubʻ niṣf in red, ǧuz' in black or red. On several folios all the red markings are missing. Additions and corrections in the margins.</note>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
